Double-Caramelized Banana Bread
  --Claire Saffitz

3 large bananas, halved lengthwise
2 tbsp + 1/3 c  sugar 
1 tbsp + 1 stick unsalted butter, melted, cooled
1/2 c sour cream, at room temperature
3 tbsp dark rum
1 tsp vanilla 
1 1/2 c ap flour
1/2 c malted milk powder
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp baking soda
1 tsp Diamond Crystal Kosher salt
1/2 c dark brown sugar 
2 large eggs, at room temperature 

Preheat griddle over medium heat and preheat oven to 350F. Peel bananas and split in half lengthwise (can cut in half for more manageable pieces). Butter the griddle with 1 tbsp, sprinkle flat side of bananas with a little sugar and place flat side down on griddle. When they develop good, dark color (not burnt) place in a medium bowl. Let them cool, then mash. Measure out a cup, reserve the rest for some other use and put the cup back into the bowl. Add sour cream and rum and mix well; set aside. In another bowl, add flour, malted milk, baking powder, baking soda, and salt; whisk to combine. Prep loaf pan by buttering and making a sling with parchment paper. In another bowl, combine sugars and eggs, whisking until mixture is very smooth (no lumps) and lightened in color. Stream in melted butter (1 stick) while continuing to whisk. Add vanilla, then half the dry ingredients, mix. Then add all of the wet mixture, whisk that in. Add the rest of the dry ingredients, switching to a rubber spatula to stir to combine. Pour into loaf pan (4.5" x 8.5"). Bake 45-60 min or until tested comes out clean, top is risen and dry. Let cool. Preheat griddle on medium-low/medium; slice 3/4" thick slices, butter griddle and put slice on. Add more butter when flipping. Serve wtih butter and/or malted whipped cream







